From: Lukas Stockner <lukas@lukasstockner.de>
Date: Sat, 14 Mar 2026 03:55:40 +0100
Subject: ipq806x: add support for Aruba AP-325

Hardware:
  SoC:      Qualcomm IPQ8068 (2x Cortex-A15)
  RAM:      512 MiB (~491 MiB usable)
  SPI-NOR:  4 MiB (SBL stages, bootloader, env, ART)
  NAND:     128 MiB (2x 32 MiB aos0/aos1, 64 MiB ubifs overlay;
                     UBI volume names enforced by APBoot)
  Ethernet: 2x Gigabit
  WiFi:     QCA9984 2.4 GHz + 5 GHz (ath10k)
  USB:      1x USB 3.0 (second port routed to internal BLE SoC,
                        disabled)
  TPM:      Atmel AT97SC3205T (uses at97sc3204t driver)
  LEDs:     power (red/green/orange), wlan (green/orange)
  Buttons:  reset

Installation is via the stock APBoot bootloader; images are
wrapped with scripts/aruba-header.py (512-byte ARUBA header +
32-bit checksum). APBoot validates the header and falls back to
the alternate aos partition on verify failure.

Co-authored-by: Florian Maurer <fmaurer@disroot.org>

